🎤 This is a PowerShell script that automatically checks and fixes internet connection problems.”
What It Does
Checks internet connection- Uses Test-Connection to ping Google’s DNS (8.8.8.8)
Fixes common issues automatically
🎤  “The script first checks if the internet is working.  If not, it runs several fixes.”
How It Fixes Issues
Restarts network adapter
Renews IP address
Flushes DNS
Resets network settings
🎤  “It basically resets everything related to networking to restore the connection.”
Final Check
Tests connection again
If fixed → success message
If not → suggests manual steps
🎤  “After fixing, it checks again. If it still fails, it tells the user what to try next.”
Why It Matters
Saves time
Automates troubleshooting
Useful for IT
🎤  “This script saves time by replacing multiple manual steps with one automated solution.”
🎤 Conclusion
“Overall, this script shows how automation can make troubleshooting faster and more efficient. Thank you.”
